<br><br>
	
<b>2012 January 28 - 29 	Takanori Kuribayashi seminar</b><br><br><br>


All aikido enthusiasts are invited to participate in this rare learning opportunity. Takanori Kuribayashi Shihan, 7th dan, from Japan Aikikai Hombu Dojo - aikido's world headquarters - will teach six special classes on 2012 January 28 and 29 (Saturday and Sunday). Full details are in the posters in the following links. Click to download and view <a href="postv3.jpg" target=_blank>TK poster01,</a> <a href="postvv4.jpg" target=_blank>TK poster02,</a> <a href="postvv6.jpg" target=_blank>TK poster03,</a> and <a href="TK4a.jpg" target=_blank>TK poster04</a>. To see the poster with the early bird discount details, click <a href="Earlybirddisc1.jpg" target=_blank>Earlybirddisc..</a><br><br><br>


<u>STREET DIRECTIONS TO SEMINAR VENUE: CLUB 650, C5 HIGHWAY, LIBIS, Q.C.</u><br><br>

A) DRIVING YOUR CAR<br><br>

Coming from the south (Makati/The Fort/Pasig/Ortigas Ave. etc), Club 650 is on the right, one lot after Shopwise and several lots before the entrance to Eastwood. Coming from the the north (UP/Ateneo/Blue Ridge area), take C-5 into Libis area and take the first u-turn opening after the Jollibee/Delifrance outlet. There is ample parking in front.<br><br>

B) USING PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION<br><br>

Club 650 is accessible via the jeeps that traverse C-5. From EDSA, get off at the Ortigas intersection, take a jeep to the Ortigas-C-5 intersection, get off at C-5 and take a second jeep north towards Eastwood. Club 650 will be on the right coming from the south (Makati/Pasig/Ortigas Ave.), and immediately beside Shopwise and before the entrance to Eastwood.<br><br>  

